Class DetermineDataTypes

  • java.lang.Object
    • DetermineDataTypes

  • public class DetermineDataTypes
extends java.lang.Object

    Determine Data Types of Numbers Entried

    This program intended to determine whether each inputed numbers from user are capable to be stored by data type(s) in Java environment, then determine which data type does the number can be stored within.

    The four major numerical data type used as a categorization in this program are byte, short, int, and long data type. Each data type has its own range capabilities to store a numerical value.

      • classificateNumbers

        public static void classificateNumbers(java.lang.String[] strNum)
        This method is used to print some messages about the data type that can be applied to T numbers of elements inputed by user before. Hence, it will print the name of some applicable data type for the numbers inputed by user. If it's not applicable due to the range value limitation of data type, it will print messages telling that the numbers can't be fitted to any data type.
        Parameters:
        strNum - This is the only parameter for classificateNumbers method
